-- S2 INVERSION (2026-07-14) — S3 (N-way) is now VACUOUS for a definer shadow, and the
-- `=>` dict is the only N-way dispatch left.  Pinned in a BUILT BINARY.
--
-- Two live impls exist and NEITHER is selected by a bare `size` inside this module: the
-- module's own `size : Int -> Int` takes every such call.  (`size (Box 3)` is now a
-- located REJECT -- the shadow gate's d3 cell pins that; a stdout gate cannot.)
--
-- But the impls are still installed and still dispatch N-way -- through `sizeOf`'s
-- written `Sizeable a =>` constraint.  That is the Fork-2 carve-out: a dict-bound
-- receiver DISPATCHES, because writing the constraint is an explicit request to resolve
-- through the interface.  For a non-operator interface it is the ONLY way to reach the
-- method from inside a shadowing module, so it is exactly the thing that must not
-- silently break.  This fixture exercises BOTH emitter arms in one program: RLocal (the
-- standalone, line 1) and RKey (the dict dispatch, lines 2-3).
interface Sizeable a where
  size : a -> Int

data Box = Box Int
data Bar = Bar Int Int

impl Sizeable Box where
  size (Box n) = n

impl Sizeable Bar where
  size (Bar a b) = a + b

size : Int -> Int
size n = n + 1

sizeOf : Sizeable a => a -> Int
sizeOf x = size x

main =
  println (size 3)
  println (sizeOf (Box 3))
  println (sizeOf (Bar 10 20))
